Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |vec4 pointLightLighting(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 47 |    // Vector iluminacin (desde vrtice a la fuente)
 48 |    vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);
 49 |    // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 50 |    float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 51 |    float specularMult = 0.0;
 52 |    if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 53 |        // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 54 |        vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 55 |        specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 56 |        specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 57 |    }
 58 |
 59 |    color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 60 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 61 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 62 |    }
 63 |    return color;-
 64 |}
 65 |
 66 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 67 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 68 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 69 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 70 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 71 |    // Si la fuente est apagada, no tenerla en cuenta
 72 |    if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 73 |        continue;
 74 |
 75 |    if (lights[i].directional) {
 76 |        // TODO
 77 |    } else {
 78 |        color = pointLightLighting(pos, N, V);
 79 |    }
 80 |    
 81 |
 82 |    return color;
 83 |}
 84 |
 85 |void main() {
 86 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 87 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 88 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 89 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 90 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 91 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 92 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 93 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 94 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 95 |}
 96 |

  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |vec4 pointLightLighting(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 47 |    // Vector iluminacin (desde vrtice a la fuente)
 48 |    vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);
 49 |    // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 50 |    float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 51 |    float specularMult = 0.0;
 52 |    if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 53 |        // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 54 |        vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 55 |        specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 56 |        specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 57 |    }
 58 |
 59 |    color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 60 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 61 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 62 |    }
 63 |    return color;
 64 |}
 65 |
 66 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 67 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 68 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 69 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 70 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 71 |    // Si la fuente est apagada, no tenerla en cuenta
 72 |    if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 73 |        continue;
 74 |
 75 |    if (lights[i].directional) {
 76 |        // TODO
 77 |    } else {
 78 |        color = pointLightLighting(pos, N, V);
 79 |    }
 80 |    
 81 |
 82 |    return color;
 83 |}
 84 |
 85 |void main() {
 86 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 87 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 88 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 89 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 90 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 91 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 92 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 93 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 94 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 95 |}
 96 |

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |vec4 pointLightLighting(light l, vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 47 |    // Vector iluminacin (desde vrtice a la fuente)
 48 |    vec3 L = normalize(vec3(l.positionEye) - pos);
 49 |    // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 50 |    float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 51 |    float specularMult = 0.0;
 52 |    if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 53 |        // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 54 |        vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 55 |        specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 56 |        specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 57 |    }
 58 |
 59 |    color += l.ambient * ambient +
 60 |                l.diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 61 |                l.specular * specular * specularMult;
 62 |    }
 63 |    return color;
 64 |}
 65 |
 66 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 67 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 68 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 69 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 70 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 71 |    // Si la fuente est apagada, no tenerla en cuenta
 72 |    if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 73 |        continue;
 74 |
 75 |    if (lights[i].directional) {
 76 |        // TODO
 77 |    } else {
 78 |        color = pointLightLighting(pos, N, V);
 79 |    }
 80 |    
 81 |    return color;
 82 |}
 83 |
 84 |void main() {
 85 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 86 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 87 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 88 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 89 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 90 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 91 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 92 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 93 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 94 |}
 95 |

 71 |                specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 72 |                specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 73 |            }
 74 |
 75 |            color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 76 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 77 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 78 |    }
 79 |    
 80 |    return color;
 81 |}
 82 |
 83 |void main() {
 84 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 85 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 86 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 87 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 88 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 89 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 90 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 91 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 92 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 93 |}

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        // Si la fuente est apagada, no tenerla en cuenta
 52 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 53 |            continue;
 54 |
 55 |        if (lights[i].directional == 1) {
 56 |            // TODO
 57 |        } else {
 58 |            // Vector iluminacin (desde vrtice a la fuente)
 59 |            vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);
 60 |            // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 61 |            float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 62 |            float specularMult = 0.0;
 63 |            if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 64 |                // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 65 |                vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 66 |                specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 67 |                specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 68 |            }
 69 |
 70 |            color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 71 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 72 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 73 |    }
 74 |    
 75 |    return color;
 76 |}
 77 |
 78 |void main() {
 79 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 80 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 81 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 82 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 83 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 84 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 85 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 86 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 87 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 88 |}
 89 |

[Sun Apr 10 00:51:20 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(58) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        // Si la fuente est apagada, no tenerla en cuenta
 52 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 53 |            continue;
 54 |
 55 |        vec3 L;
 56 |        if (lights[i].directional == 1) {
 57 |            // TODO
 58 |            L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye);
 59 |        } else {
 60 |            // Vector iluminacin (desde vrtice a la fuente)
 61 |            L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);
 62 |        }
 63 |            // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 64 |            float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 65 |            float specularMult = 0.0;
 66 |            if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 67 |                // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 68 |                vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 69 |                specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 70 |                specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 71 |            }
 72 |
 73 |            color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 74 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 75 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 76 |    }
 77 |    
 78 |    return color;
 79 |}
 80 |
 81 |void main() {
 82 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 83 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 84 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 85 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 86 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 87 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 88 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 89 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 90 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 91 |}
 92 |

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos * !lights[i].directional);
 55 |        
 56 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 57 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 58 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 59 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 60 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 61 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 62 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 63 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 64 |        }
 65 |
 66 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 67 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 68 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 69 |    }
 70 |    
 71 |    return color;
 72 |}
 73 |
 74 |void main() {
 75 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 76 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 77 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 78 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 79 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 80 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 81 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 82 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 83 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 84 |}
 85 |

 16 |  int directional;

 24 |};

 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |

 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        if (lights[i].directional) {
 55 |            L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye));
 56 |        } else {
 57 |            L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);

 64 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 65 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 66 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 67 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 68 |        }
 69 |
 70 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 71 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 72 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 73 |    }
 74 |    
 75 |    return color;
 76 |}

  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        vec3 L;
 55 |        if (lights[i].directional) {
 56 |            L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye));
 57 |        } else {
 58 |            L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) - pos);
 59 |        }
 60 |        
 61 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 62 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 63 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 64 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 65 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 66 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 67 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 68 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 69 |        }
 70 |
 71 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 72 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 73 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 74 |    }
 75 |    
 76 |    return color;
 77 |}
 78 |
 79 |void main() {
 80 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 81 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 82 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 83 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 84 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 85 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 86 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 87 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 88 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 89 |}
 90 |

[Sun Apr 10 01:06:36 2022] INF: [uboMaterial.cpp (54)] UBO Material creado
[Sun Apr 10 01:06:36 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 01:06:36 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(70) : error C1115: unable to find compatible overloaded function "dot(float, vec3)"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 68 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 69 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 70 |        color *= dot(lights[i].spotCutoff, pos);
 71 |    }
 72 |    
 73 |    return color;
 74 |}
 75 |
 76 |void main() {
 77 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 78 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 79 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 80 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 81 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 82 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 83 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 84 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 85 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 86 |}
 87 |

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 68 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 69 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 70 |        if (dot(vec3(lights[i].positionEye), pos) > radians(lights[i].spotCutoff))
 71 |            color *= spotValue;
 72 |    }
 73 |    
 74 |    return color;
 75 |}
 76 |
 77 |void main() {
 78 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 79 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 80 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 81 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 82 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 83 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 84 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 85 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 86 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 87 |}
 88 |

[Sun Apr 10 01:14:20 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(68) : error C1009: "normal" is not member of struct "LightSource"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(vec3(lights[i].positionEye) + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |
 68 |        if (dot(vec3(lights[i].normal), pos) > radians(lights[i].spotCutoff) && lights[i].spotCutoff < 180)
 69 |            color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 70 |                lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 71 |                lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 72 |    }
 73 |    
 74 |    return color;
 75 |}
 76 |
 77 |void main() {
 78 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 79 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 80 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 81 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 82 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 83 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 84 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 85 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 86 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 87 |}
 88 |

[Sun Apr 10 01:43:26 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 01:43:26 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(73) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"
0(74) : error C1009: "spotDirection" is not member of struct "LightSource"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 69 |            if (dot(vec3(lights[i].positionEye), pos) < radians(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 70 |                spot = 0.0;
 71 |            }
 72 |            else {
 73 |                vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].positionEye);
 74 |                spot = max(Lp - lights[i].spotDirection, 0.0);
 75 |            }
 76 |        }
 77 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 78 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 79 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 80 |        color *= spot;
 81 |    }
 82 |    
 83 |    return color;
 84 |}
 85 |
 86 |void main() {
 87 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 88 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 89 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 90 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 91 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 92 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 93 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 94 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 95 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 96 |}
 97 |

 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 69 |            if (dot(vec3(lights[i].positionEye), pos) < radians(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 70 |                spot = 0.0;
 71 |            }
 72 |            else {
 73 |                vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].positionEye.xyz);
 74 |                spot = max(Lp - lights[i].spotDirectionWorld, 0.0);
 75 |            }
 76 |        }
 77 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 78 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 79 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 80 |        color *= spot;
 81 |    }
 82 |    
 83 |    return color;
 84 |}
 85 |
 86 |void main() {
 87 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 88 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 89 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 90 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 91 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 92 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 93 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 94 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 95 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 96 |}
 97 |

[Sun Apr 10 01:53:31 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 01:53:31 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(84) : error C0000: syntax error, unexpected '{', expecting ',' or ';' at token "{"
0(90) : error C1038: declaration of "V" conflicts with previous declaration at 0(47)
0(47) : error C1004: in and out can't be used on local variable "V"
0(92) : error C1503: undefined variable "eN"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 68 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 69 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 70 |
 71 |        float spot = 1.0;
 72 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 73 |            vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].positionEye.xyz);
 74 |            spot = max(distance(Lp,  lights[i].spotDirectionWorld), 0.0);
 75 |            if (spot < cos(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 76 |                spot = 0.0;
 77 |        }
 78 |        color *= spot;
 79 |    }
 80 |    
 81 |    return color;
 82 |}
 83 |
 84 |void main() {
 85 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 86 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 87 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 88 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 89 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 90 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 91 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 92 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 93 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 94 |}
 95 |

[Sun Apr 10 01:57:10 2022] INF: [uboMaterial.cpp (54)] UBO Material creado
[Sun Apr 10 01:57:10 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 01:57:10 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(73) : error C1009: "position" is not member of struct "LightSource"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        color += lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 68 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 69 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 70 |
 71 |        float spot = 1.0;
 72 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 73 |            vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].position.xyz);
 74 |            spot = max(distance(Lp,  lights[i].spotDirectionWorld), 0.0);
 75 |            if (spot < cos(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 76 |                spot = 0.0;
 77 |            }
 78 |        }
 79 |        color *= spot;
 80 |    }
 81 |    
 82 |    return color;
 83 |}
 84 |
 85 |void main() {
 86 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 87 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 88 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 89 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 90 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 91 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 92 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 93 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 94 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 95 |}
 96 |

[Sun Apr 10 12:07:10 2022] INF: [uboMaterial.cpp (54)] UBO Material creado
[Sun Apr 10 12:07:10 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 12:07:10 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(78) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"
0(79) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"
0(80) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 69 |            vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 70 |            spot = max(distance(Lp,  lights[i].spotDirectionWorld), 0.0);
 71 |            if (spot < cos(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 72 |                spot = 0.0;
 73 |            }
 74 |        }
 75 |
 76 |
 77 |        color += spot * lights[i].attenuation +
 78 |            lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 79 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 80 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 81 |
 82 |    }
 83 |    
 84 |    return color;
 85 |}
 86 |
 87 |void main() {
 88 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 89 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 90 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 91 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 92 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 93 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 94 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 95 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 96 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 97 |}
 98 |

[Sun Apr 10 12:11:51 2022] INF: [uboMaterial.cpp (54)] UBO Material creado

[Sun Apr 10 12:11:51 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(76) : error C7011: implicit cast from "vec4" to "vec3"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye - pos. Else, just positionEye
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180) {
 69 |            vec3 Lp = normalize(pos - lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 70 |            spot = max(distance(Lp,  lights[i].spotDirectionWorld), 0.0);
 71 |            if (spot < cos(lights[i].spotCutoff)) {
 72 |                spot = 0.0;
 73 |            }
 74 |        }
 75 |
 76 |        float d = distance(lights[i].positionWorld, pos);
 77 |        float attenuation = 1.0 / (max(1, lights[i].attenuation.x + lights[i].attenuation.y * d + lights[i].attenuation.z * d * d));
 78 |
 79 |        color += spot * attenuation +
 80 |            lights[i].ambient * ambient +
 81 |            lights[i].diffuse * diffuse * diffuseMult +
 82 |            lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult;
 83 |
 84 |    }
 85 |    
 86 |    return color;
 87 |}
 88 |
 89 |void main() {
 90 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 91 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 92 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 93 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 94 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 95 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 96 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
 97 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
 98 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
 99 |}
100 |

[Sun Apr 10 16:22:38 2022] INF: [uboLightSources.cpp (86)] UBO LightSources creado
[Sun Apr 10 16:22:38 2022] INF: [bufferObject.cpp (41)] Buffer object 24 ha reservado 80 bytes
[Sun Apr 10 16:22:38 2022] INF: [uboMaterial.cpp (54)] UBO Material creado
[Sun Apr 10 16:22:38 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/gouraud.vert
[Sun Apr 10 16:22:38 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(82) : error C0000: syntax error, unexpected ')', expecting ',' or ';' at token ")"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye. Else -> positionEye - pos
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180 && lights[i].directional == 1) {
 69 |            spot = max(dot(L,  lights[i].spotDirectionWorld), 0.0);
 70 |
 71 |            bool inside = spot >= cos(radians(lights[i].spotCutoff)) 
 72 |                        && spot == lights[i].spotCosCutoff;
 73 |            if (inside) { // TODO all vertices are outside the cone???
 74 |                spot = pow(spot, lights[i].spotExponent);
 75 |            } else {
 76 |                spot = 0.0;
 77 |            }
 78 |        }
 79 |
 80 |        float d = distance(pos, lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 81 |        float attenuation = 1.0 / max(1, 
 82 |            lights[i].attenuation.x + lights[i].attenuation.y * d + lights[i].attenuation.z * d * d));
 83 |
 84 |        color += spot * attenuation 
 85 |               * (lights[i].ambient  * ambient 
 86 |               +  lights[i].diffuse  * diffuse  * diffuseMult 
 87 |               +  lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult);
 88 |    }
 89 |    
 90 |    return color;
 91 |}
 92 |
 93 |void main() {
 94 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 95 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 96 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 97 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 98 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 99 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
100 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
101 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
102 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
103 |}
104 |

[Sun Apr 10 16:27:07 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(69) : error C1009: "spotDirectioneye" is not member of struct "LightSource"

Vertex shader: ../p5/gouraud.vert
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |layout (std140, binding=0) uniform GLMatrices {
  4 |  mat4 modelMatrix;
  5 |  mat4 viewMatrix;
  6 |  mat4 projMatrix;
  7 |  mat4 modelviewMatrix;
  8 |  mat4 modelviewprojMatrix;
  9 |  mat3 normalMatrix;
 10 |};
 11 |struct LightSource {
 12 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
 13 |  vec4 positionWorld;
 14 |  vec4 positionEye;
 15 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
 16 |  int directional;
 17 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 18 |  int enabled;
 19 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 20 |  vec3 attenuation;
 21 |};
 22 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 23 |  LightSource lights[4];
 24 |};
 25 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 26 |vec4 diffuse;
 27 |vec4 ambient;
 28 |vec4 specular;
 29 |vec4 emissive;
 30 |float shininess;
 31 |int textureCount;
 32 |};
 33 |
 34 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 35 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 36 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 37 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 38 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 39 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 40 |
 41 |in vec4 position;
 42 |in vec3 normal;
 43 |
 44 |out vec4 color;
 45 |
 46 |// Suponiendo fuentes puntuales
 47 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 48 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 49 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 50 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 51 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 52 |            continue;
 53 |
 54 |        // If directional -> positionEye. Else -> positionEye - pos
 55 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 56 |        
 57 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 58 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 59 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 60 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 61 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 62 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 63 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 64 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 65 |        }
 66 |
 67 |        float spot = 1.0;
 68 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180 && lights[i].directional == 1) {
 69 |            spot = max(dot(-L,  lights[i].spotDirectioneye), 0.0);
 70 |
 71 |            bool inside = spot >= cos(radians(lights[i].spotCutoff)) 
 72 |                        && spot == lights[i].spotCosCutoff;
 73 |            if (inside) { // TODO all vertices are outside the cone???
 74 |                spot = pow(spot, lights[i].spotExponent);
 75 |            } else {
 76 |                spot = 0.0;
 77 |            }
 78 |        }
 79 |
 80 |        float d = distance(pos, lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 81 |        float attenuation = 1.0 / max(1, 
 82 |            lights[i].attenuation.x + lights[i].attenuation.y * d + lights[i].attenuation.z * d * d);
 83 |        if (lights[i].directional == 0)
 84 |            attenuation = 1.0; // TODO optimize this
 85 |
 86 |        color += spot * attenuation 
 87 |               * (lights[i].ambient  * ambient 
 88 |               +  lights[i].diffuse  * diffuse  * diffuseMult 
 89 |               +  lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult);
 90 |    }
 91 |    
 92 |    return color;
 93 |}
 94 |
 95 |void main() {
 96 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 97 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 98 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 99 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
100 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
101 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
102 |  // Clculo de la iluminacin
103 |  color = iluminacion(eposition, eN, V);
104 |  gl_Position = modelviewprojMatrix * position;
105 |}
106 |

[Sun Apr 10 16:43:30 2022] INF: [shader.cpp (169)] Compilando ../p5/phong.frag
[Sun Apr 10 16:43:30 2022] ERR: [program.cpp (223)] Error compilando el shader:0(89) : error C1503: undefined variable "normalMatrix"
0(89) : error C1503: undefined variable "normal"
0(91) : error C1503: undefined variable "modelviewMatrix"
0(91) : error C1503: undefined variable "position"
0(94) : error C1103: too few parameters in function call

Fragment shader: ../p5/phong.frag
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |struct LightSource {
  4 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
  5 |  vec4 positionWorld;
  6 |  vec4 positionEye;
  7 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
  8 |  int directional;
  9 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 10 |  int enabled;
 11 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 12 |  vec3 attenuation;
 13 |};
 14 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 15 |  LightSource lights[4];
 16 |};
 17 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 18 |vec4 diffuse;
 19 |vec4 ambient;
 20 |vec4 specular;
 21 |vec4 emissive;
 22 |float shininess;
 23 |int textureCount;
 24 |};
 25 |
 26 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 27 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 28 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 29 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 30 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 31 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 32 |
 33 |in vec4 color;
 34 |in vec3 fragN;
 35 |in vec3 fragPosition;
 36 |
 37 |out vec4 fragColor;
 38 |
 39 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 40 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 41 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 42 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 43 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 44 |            continue;
 45 |
 46 |        // If directional -> positionEye. Else -> positionEye - pos
 47 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 48 |        
 49 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 50 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 51 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 52 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 53 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 54 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 55 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 56 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 57 |        }
 58 |        
 59 |        float spot = 1.0;
 60 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180 && lights[i].directional == 0) {
 61 |            spot = max(dot(-L, lights[i].spotDirectionEye), 0.0);
 62 |
 63 |            bool inside = spot >= lights[i].spotCosCutoff;
 64 |            if (inside) {
 65 |                spot = pow(spot, lights[i].spotExponent);
 66 |            } else {
 67 |                spot = 0.0;
 68 |            }
 69 |            
 70 |        }
 71 |
 72 |        float d = distance(pos, lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 73 |        float attenuation = 1.0 / max(1, 
 74 |            lights[i].attenuation.x + lights[i].attenuation.y * d + lights[i].attenuation.z * d * d);
 75 |        if (lights[i].directional == 0)
 76 |            attenuation = 1.0; // TODO optimize this
 77 |
 78 |        color += spot * attenuation 
 79 |               * (lights[i].ambient  * ambient 
 80 |               +  lights[i].diffuse  * diffuse  * diffuseMult 
 81 |               +  lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult);
 82 |    }
 83 |    
 84 |    return color;
 85 |}
 86 |
 87 |void main() {
 88 |  // Normal en el espacio de la cmara
 89 |  vec3 eN = normalize(normalMatrix * normal);
 90 |  // Vrtice en el espacio de la cmara
 91 |  vec3 eposition = vec3(modelviewMatrix * position);
 92 |  // Vector vista (desde vrtice a la cmara)
 93 |  vec3 V = normalize(-eposition.xyz);
 94 |  fragColor = iluminacion();
 95 |}
 96 |

Fragment shader: ../p5/phong.frag
---------------------------------
  1 |#version 420
  2 |
  3 |struct LightSource {
  4 |  vec4 ambient, diffuse, specular;
  5 |  vec4 positionWorld;
  6 |  vec4 positionEye;
  7 |  vec3 spotDirectionWorld;
  8 |  int directional;
  9 |  vec3 spotDirectionEye;
 10 |  int enabled;
 11 |  float spotExponent, spotCutoff, spotCosCutoff;
 12 |  vec3 attenuation;
 13 |};
 14 |layout (std140, binding=2) uniform Lights {
 15 |  LightSource lights[4];
 16 |};
 17 |layout (std140, binding=1) uniform Material {
 18 |vec4 diffuse;
 19 |vec4 ambient;
 20 |vec4 specular;
 21 |vec4 emissive;
 22 |float shininess;
 23 |int textureCount;
 24 |};
 25 |
 26 |uint numDiffTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 0, 3); }
 27 |uint numSpecTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 3, 3); }
 28 |uint numNormTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 6, 3); }
 29 |uint numHeightTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 9, 3); }
 30 |uint numOpacTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 12, 3); }
 31 |uint numAmbTextures() { return bitfieldExtract(textureCount, 15, 3); }
 32 |
 33 |in vec4 color;
 34 |in vec3 fragN;
 35 |in vec3 fragPosition;
 36 |
 37 |out vec4 fragColor;
 38 |
 39 |vec4 iluminacion(vec3 pos, vec3 N, vec3 V) {
 40 |    // Componente emisiva del material
 41 |    vec4 color = emissive;
 42 |    for (int i = 0; i < lights.length(); i++) {
 43 |        if (lights[i].enabled == 0)
 44 |            continue;
 45 |
 46 |        // If directional -> positionEye. Else -> positionEye - pos
 47 |        vec3 L = normalize(lights[i].positionEye.xyz + pos * (lights[i].directional - 1));
 48 |        
 49 |        // Multiplicador de la componente difusa
 50 |        float diffuseMult = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);
 51 |        float specularMult = 0.0;
 52 |        if (diffuseMult > 0.0) {
 53 |            // Multiplicador de la componente especular
 54 |            vec3 R = reflect(-L, N);
 55 |            specularMult = max(0.0, dot(R, V));
 56 |            specularMult = pow(specularMult, shininess);
 57 |        }
 58 |        
 59 |        float spot = 1.0;
 60 |        if (lights[i].spotCutoff < 180 && lights[i].directional == 0) {
 61 |            spot = max(dot(-L, lights[i].spotDirectionEye), 0.0);
 62 |
 63 |            bool inside = spot >= lights[i].spotCosCutoff;
 64 |            if (inside) {
 65 |                spot = pow(spot, lights[i].spotExponent);
 66 |            } else {
 67 |                spot = 0.0;
 68 |            }
 69 |            
 70 |        }
 71 |
 72 |        float d = distance(pos, lights[i].positionWorld.xyz);
 73 |        float attenuation = 1.0 / max(1, 
 74 |            lights[i].attenuation.x + lights[i].attenuation.y * d + lights[i].attenuation.z * d * d);
 75 |        if (lights[i].directional == 0)
 76 |            attenuation = 1.0; // TODO optimize this
 77 |
 78 |        color += spot * attenuation 
 79 |               * (lights[i].ambient  * ambient 
 80 |               +  lights[i].diffuse  * diffuse  * diffuseMult 
 81 |               +  lights[i].specular * specular * specularMult);
 82 |    }
 83 |    
 84 |    return color;
 85 |}
 86 |
 87 |void main() {
 88 |  vec3 eN = normalize(fragN);
 89 |  vec3 V = normalize(-fragPosition.xyz);
 90 |  fragColor = iluminacion();
 91 |}
 92 |
